Package: surrogateTransportability
Type: Package
Title: Surrogate Inference via Random Probability Distributions
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: person("Author", "Name", email = "author@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements surrogate marker evaluation using random probability distributions
    to assess transportability across future studies. Provides both total variation (TV) ball
    and Wasserstein ball minimax approaches with RF-ensemble type-level inference. The TV-ball
    approach provides conservative bounds for arbitrary distributional changes, while the
    Wasserstein ball approach offers tighter bounds for covariate shift scenarios. Both achieve
    validated <2% approximation error. The method models future studies as draws from constraint
    sets around the current study, enabling robust inference about surrogate quality across
    diverse future populations.
